.Dd March 14, 2026
.Dt MD 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm md
.Nd query and transform Markdown files
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Ar program
.Op Fl -json
.Op Fl -dir Ar directory
.Op Fl i
.Op Ar file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
evaluates a jq-inspired DSL program against a Markdown file.
It parses Markdown leniently, preferring best-effort results over strict errors.
.Pp
If no
.Ar file
is given,
.Nm
reads from standard input.
.Pp
Plain text output is the default.
Use
.Fl -json
for structured output.
.Sh DSL
The DSL uses pipelines to chain operations.
Each stage receives the output of the previous stage.
.Ss Extractors
Extractors pull structured data from the document.
When piped a string, extractors parse that string
instead of the original document.
.Bl -tag -width "frontmatter"
.It Ic frontmatter
YAML or TOML frontmatter as a record.
Fields depend on the document content.
Returns null if no frontmatter is present.
.It Ic body
Document body without frontmatter, as a string.
.It Ic headings
Array of ATX headings.
Each record contains:
.Li .depth
(integer 1\(en6),
.Li .text
(heading text without leading hashes),
.Li .line
(line number),
.Li .source
(raw heading line).
.It Ic links
Array of links found in the document.
Each record contains:
.Li .kind
(standard, wikilink, image, or embed),
.Li .target
(URL or link target),
.Li .text
(display text),
.Li .line
(line number),
.Li .source
(raw link syntax).
.It Ic tags
Deduplicated array of inline
.Li #tag
occurrences.
Each record contains:
.Li .name ,
.Li .line ,
.Li .source
(raw tag including #).
.It Ic codeblocks
Array of fenced and indented code blocks.
Each record contains:
.Li .language ,
.Li .content ,
.Li .start_line ,
.Li .end_line ,
.Li .source
(entire block including fence lines).
.It Ic stats
Word and line counts for the document body (excluding frontmatter).
Record contains:
.Li .lines
and
.Li .words .
.It Ic comments
Array of HTML and Obsidian comments.
Each record contains:
.Li .kind
(html or obsidian),
.Li .text ,
.Li .line ,
.Li .source
(raw comment including delimiters).
.It Ic footnotes
Array of footnote definitions.
Each record contains:
.Li .label ,
.Li .text ,
.Li .line ,
.Li .source
(raw definition line).
.It Ic nodes
Array of block-level document nodes.
Each record contains:
.Li .type
(heading, paragraph, codeblock, comment, or footnote),
.Li .text ,
.Li .line ,
.Li .source .
Type-specific fields:
.Li .depth
for headings,
.Li .language
for codeblocks,
.Li .kind
for comments,
.Li .label
for footnotes.
The
.Li .source
field covers the full block extent
(structural syntax + content + trailing whitespace).
Consecutive nodes' sources tile contiguously across the body.
.It Ic incoming
Array of files linking to the input file.
Requires
.Fl -dir
or a file argument.
Each record contains:
.Li .source
(path of the linking file),
.Li .kind
(link kind),
.Li .line
(line number in the source file).
.El
.Ss Field Access
Use
.Li .field
to access record fields. Nested access:
.Li .author.name .
.Ss Filtering
.Bl -tag -width "skip_until(pred)"
.It Ic select(predicate)
Filter arrays by predicate.
When applied to a single value, returns the value if the predicate
is true, or null otherwise.
Predicates support comparisons
.Pq Li "==, !=, <, >, <=, >=" ,
boolean logic
.Pq Li "and, or, not" ,
and string functions
.Pq Li "contains(), startswith()" .
.It Ic skip_until(predicate)
Drop array elements until the predicate matches.
The matching element is excluded; elements after it are returned.
.It Ic take_until(predicate)
Take array elements until the predicate matches.
The matching element is excluded.
If no element matches, the entire array is returned.
.El
.Pp
.Ic skip_until
and
.Ic take_until
compose for positional queries on
.Ic nodes .
.Ss Predicate Functions
.Bl -tag -width "startswith(.field, prefix)"
.It Ic contains(.field, substring)
Test whether a string field contains the given substring.
Returns a boolean.
.It Ic startswith(.field, prefix)
Test whether a string field starts with the given prefix.
Returns a boolean.
.El
.Ss List Operations
.Bl -tag -width "group(.field)"
.It Ic first
First element of an array.
Returns null for an empty array.
On non-array input, returns the input unchanged.
.It Ic last
Last element of an array.
Returns null for an empty array.
On non-array input, returns the input unchanged.
.It Ic count
Length of an array, string (byte count), or record (number of keys).
Returns 1 for other types.
.It Ic reverse
Reverse the order of an array.
On non-array input, returns the input unchanged.
.It Ic map(.field)
Extract a field from each element of an array.
Returns an array of the extracted values.
.It Ic unique
Remove duplicate values from an array.
Preserves the order of first occurrences.
.It Ic sort(.field)
Sort an array by a field value.
On non-array input, returns the input unchanged.
.It Ic group(.field)
Group array elements into a record keyed by field value.
Each key maps to an array of elements sharing that value.
.El
.Ss Record Operations
.Bl -tag -width "has(name)"
.It Ic keys
List record keys as an array of strings.
.It Ic has(name)
Check if a record contains a field with the given name.
Returns a boolean.
.El
.Ss Format Conversion
.Bl -tag -width "yaml"
.It Ic yaml
Convert between records and YAML text.
When given a record, serializes it to YAML.
When given a string, parses it as YAML into a record.
.It Ic toml
Convert between records and TOML text.
When given a record, serializes it to TOML.
When given a string, parses it as TOML into a record.
.El
.Ss Mutation
.Bl -tag -width "set(.field, value)"
.It Ic set(.field, value)
Set a frontmatter field.
Produces the modified document as a string.
.It Ic del(.field)
Delete a frontmatter field.
Produces the modified document as a string.
.It Ic .field += [values]
Append values to a frontmatter array field.
If the field is null, creates it with the given array.
If the field is an array, concatenates the values.
Produces the modified document as a string.
.It Ic replace(text)
Replace a span in the document with the given text.
Works on body strings (from
.Ic body ) ,
and any record or array of records with a
.Li .source
field \(em including output from
.Ic nodes , headings , links , tags , codeblocks , comments ,
and
.Ic footnotes .
Produces the modified document as a string.
.It Ic append(text)
Insert text after a span in the document.
Accepts the same inputs as
.Ic replace .
Produces the modified document as a string.
.El
.Ss Link Validation
These functions require
.Fl -dir
or a file argument to resolve paths.
.Bl -tag -width "resolve"
.It Ic exists
Add an
.Li .exists
boolean field to each link record, indicating whether the link target
exists on disk.
Accepts a single link record or an array of link records.
.It Ic resolve
Add a
.Li .path
field to each link record with the resolved filesystem path.
Accepts a single link record or an array of link records.
.El
.Ss Comma Operator
Multiple outputs from the same input:
.Li "(.title, .draft)" .
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -json
Output in JSON format.
.It Fl -dir Ar directory
Directory for
.Ic incoming ,
.Ic exists ,
and
.Ic resolve .
.It Fl i
Edit the file in-place. The program must produce a document string.
.It Fl h , Fl -help
Show usage information.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh EXAMPLES
Get a frontmatter field:
.Dl md 'frontmatter | .title' notes.md
.Pp
List h2 headings:
.Dl md 'headings | select(.depth == 2)' notes.md
.Pp
Count wikilinks:
.Dl md 'links | select(.kind == \&"wikilink\&") | count' notes.md
.Pp
Set a frontmatter field in-place:
.Dl md 'frontmatter | set(.draft, false)' -i notes.md
.Pp
Delete a frontmatter field:
.Dl md 'frontmatter | del(.tags)' -i notes.md
.Pp
Extract content under a heading using nodes:
.Dl md 'nodes | skip_until(.text == \&"API\&") | take_until(.type == \&"heading\&")' notes.md
.Pp
Find broken links:
.Dl md 'links | exists | select(.exists == false)' --dir ./vault/ notes.md
.Pp
Find incoming links:
.Dl md 'incoming' --dir ./vault/ notes.md
.Pp
JSON output:
.Dl md 'headings' --json notes.md
.Pp
Append to a frontmatter array:
.Dl md 'frontmatter | .tags += [\&"new-tag\&"]' -i notes.md
.Pp
Replace a section's content:
.Dl md 'nodes | skip_until(.text == \&"Notes\&") | take_until(.type == \&"heading\&") | replace(\&"Updated.\en\&")' -i notes.md
.Pp
Append after a section:
.Dl md 'nodes | skip_until(.text == \&"Notes\&") | take_until(.type == \&"heading\&") | append(\&"More.\en\&")' -i notes.md
.Pp
Replace entire body:
.Dl md 'body | replace(\&"New content.\en\&")' -i notes.md
.Pp
Replace a heading directly:
.Dl md 'headings | first | replace(\&"# New Title\&")' -i notes.md
.Pp
Insert content after an Obsidian comment marker:
.Dl md 'comments | select(contains(.text, \&"begin notes\&")) | first | append(\&"\enNew note.\en\&")' -i notes.md
.Pp
Extract content between comment markers:
.Dl md 'nodes | skip_until(.type == \&"comment\&" and contains(.text, \&"begin\&")) | take_until(.type == \&"comment\&" and contains(.text, \&"end\&"))' notes.md
.Pp
Read from stdin:
.Dl cat notes.md | md 'tags | map(.name) | unique'
.Pp
Process all files in a vault:
.Dl find vault/ -name '*.md' -exec md 'frontmatter | .title' {} \e;
.Sh SUPPORTED FORMATS
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Standard Markdown links:
.Li [text](url)
.It
Obsidian wikilinks:
.Li [[target]] ,
.Li [[target|alias]]
.It
Image and embed links:
.Li ![alt](url) ,
.Li ![[embed]]
.It
YAML frontmatter (delimited by
.Li --- )
.It
TOML frontmatter (delimited by
.Li +++ )
.It
ATX headings
.Pq Li "# H1"
through
.Li "###### H6"
.It
Fenced code blocks (backtick and tilde)
.It
Indented code blocks (4+ spaces or tab)
.It
Inline tags
.Pq Li #tag
.It
HTML comments
.Pq Li "<!-- ... -->"
.It
Obsidian comments
.Pq Li "%% ... %%"
.It
Footnote definitions
.Pq Li "[^label]: text"
.El
